[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa was formerly known as the NorthWest Frontier Province (NWFP). It has a border with the Federally Administered Tribal Areas (FATA) to its west and south, Gilgit-Baltistan to its northeast, Azad Kashmir on the east, and Punjab and the Islamabad Capital Territory on its southeast. It borders with the province of Balochistan to its south, and Afghanistan to its northwest.

For a map of Pakistan showing administrative divisions, see http://www.technologijos.lt/upload/image/n/zmoniu_pasaulis/redakcijos_akiratis/straipsnis-10705/nuotrauka-23281/pakadmin.jpg. - Mod.MPP]

