[2] Global update: Polio Eradication Initiative
Date: Thu 21 Mar 2013
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative [excerpted, edited]
http://polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx


Global Polio Eradication Initiative update as of 20 Mar 2012
------------------------------------------------------------
Total cases
Year-to-date 2013 / Year-to-date 2012 / Total in 2012
Globally: 11 / 31 / 223
- in endemic countries: 11 / 29 / 217
- in non-endemic countries: 0 / 2 / 6

Case breakdown by country
Country: Year-to-date 2013 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Year-to-date 2012 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Total in 2012 / Date of most recent case
Pakistan: 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 12 / 1 / 1 / 14 // 58 / 12 Feb 2013
Afghanistan: 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 37 / 31 Jan 2013
Nigeria: 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 7 / 3 / 0 / 10 // 122 / 13 Feb 2013
Chad: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 5 / 14 Jun 2012
Niger: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 15 Nov 2012
Total: 11 / 0 / 0 / 11 // 26 / 4 / 1 / 31 // 223 //
Total in endemic countries: 11/ 0 / 0 / 11 // 24 / 4 / 1 / 31 // 217
Total outbreak: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 2 / 0 / 0 / 2 // 6

*Data in WHO as of 21 Mar 2012 for 2012 data and 19 Mar 2013 for 2013 data

In 2013, no WPV3 cases have been reported. Over the past 6 months, only 2 cases due to this strain were reported worldwide (both in Nigeria, the most recent had onset of paralysis on [10 Nov 2013]). In Asia, no WPV3 cases have been reported since last April [2012]. It is the lowest levels of WPV3 transmission ever recorded.

Afghanistan
-----------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2013 remains 1. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 37. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [31 Jan 2013] (WPV1 from Nangarhar).
- No new circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDVP2 cases remains 9 for 2012, and one for 2013. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [22 Jan 2013] (from Hilmand).

Nigeria
- One new WPV case was reported in the past week (WPV1 from Bauchi), bringing the total number of WPV cases for 2013 to 5. It is the most recent case in the country and had onset of paralysis on [13 Feb 2013]. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 122.
- No new cases of cVDPV2 were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 8. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [24 Nov 2012] (from Kebbi).

Pakistan
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2013 remains 5. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 58. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [12 Feb 2013] (from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa - KP).
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2013 remains 1. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 16. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [11 Jan 2013] (from Balochistan).
- The security situation continues to be monitored closely, in consultation with law enforcement agencies. Immunization activities continue to be implemented, in some areas staggered or postponed, depending on the security situation at the local level.

Chad
----
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 5 (no WPV cases in 2013). The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [14 Jun 2012] (WPV1 from Lac).
- One new cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week, with onset of paralysis on [4 Feb 2013] (from Salamat, in the east of the country). It is the 1st cVDPV2 case in Chad in 2013. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 12.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
--------------------------------------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [20 Dec 2011] (WPV1 from Maniema). DR Congo is no longer considered to have re-established WPV transmission.
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 17. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [4 Apr 2012] (from Katanga).

Horn of Africa
--------------
- No new cases were reported in the past week. The most recent case was a cVDPV2 case from Somalia, with onset of paralysis on [9 Jan 2013].
- Outbreak response is continuing in various parts of the Horn of Africa, in response to the ongoing cVDPV2 outbreak in south-central Somalia.

West Africa
-----------
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recent case in the region was a WPV1 from Tahoua province in Niger with onset of paralysis on [15 Nov 2012]. It is the only case in the region in 2012 (barring Nigeria), and has been covered by 3 immunization campaigns.

